It was started by Marius Bakkes who wanted to know whether the old “station” pie and gravy still existed. Since then, Thea Rix has taken the Gravy Train to various restaurants in order to find the perfect gravy and most delicious pie. It started small, but has now grown to approximately 30 people, once a month riding the Lowveld Pie, Chips and Gravy Train. ALSO READ: Huis Maré vier vroue met finesse The famous opening “toot toot” is done by Dave Walters at every gathering. Enquiries: Rix on 082-771-2889. ALSO READ: De Hallen offers convenience and luxury like never before